"{\n  \"text\": \"Hey everybody. I went and talked to Tim and Leanne over at Memorial Villages Farmers Market uh last weekend. Uh it's Monday. I talked to him on Saturday, and I talked to him Saturday before that, Saturday before that. But uh we're kind of keeping up to date with each other, and I think I'm ready to start it this upcoming week. And if not this week, the weekend after that. And my tomatoes I've been chopping off the vine. They're green, but they're giant, and I don't want them to burst and bulge and become too much on the vine. So I took them off a little bit early. I'm not letting them, I'm gonna let them fully ripen and redden in bags, uh, and a lot of the other smaller stuff that can handle it. I'm gonna fully ripen on the vines, of course. And uh that's gonna be my main product, and I'll have a bunch of babbook and noosh that I have from eggplant that I grew, and I'll have a bunch of fermented cucumber salad that I will be selling. And other than that, I'll have a spattering of herbs and spattering of green beans and some other products, and really just a sign saying, hey, I'm growing food, and I'm gonna try to get better at this. I'm gonna try to have more food, more diversity later. I'm gonna have more herbs and some of this stuff. But uh, I just want to start talking to people. I want to get out there, I want to do my thing. Uh also I'm thinking about maybe talking to Tim and Leanne about collecting some compost. So back to you on those details once I talk to all that. I'm just too excited not to share a little bit of that. Anyway, uh start this weekend, and if not this weekend, next weekend. Uh wish me luck, y'all. Here we go. Uh\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hey everybody.\",\n      \"start\": 0.96,\n      \"end\": 2.16,\n      \"duration\": 1.2,\n      \"confidence\": 0.976,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" He\",\n          \"start\": 0.96,\n          \"end\": 1.28,\n          \"duration\": 0.32,\n